OL,3,C'Serious failures' by social worker as
OL,4,Cdoctor stabbed mother to death
OL,6,FCoroner Mark Harris told the court
OL,7,Fthat had social worker "Lisa Chapman
OL,8,Facted as she should have done ... it
OL,9,Fis probable that Andrew would have
OL,10,Fbeen admitted to hospital before he
OL,11,Fkilled his mother".
OL,13,FMr Harris explained that she wrongly
OL,14,Fdismissed concerns raised by two
OL,15,Fdoctors who knew him well and
OL,16,F"knowingly delayed taking any steps to
OL,17,Fsecure Andrew's admission" to
OL,18,Fcompulsory medical care.
