OL,6,F"We wish to assure the Nisbet family
OL,7,Fand those using our services that we
OL,8,Fare determined to continue to make
OL,9,Fimprovements in our systems and
OL,10,Fprocesses within the mental health
OL,11,Fservices."
OL,13,FAndrew Nisbet pleaded guilty to
OL,14,Fmanslaughter on the grounds of
OL,15,Fdiminished responsibility and is now
OL,16,Fbeing held at a secure mental health
OL,17,Ffacility in England.
